Toulouse and Springbok player Cheslin Kolbe. JOHANNESBURG - Cheslin Kolbe has bagged yet another accolade. The 2019 Rugby World Cup winner was named the Top 14's player of the season on Monday in Paris. The 26-year old won the Webb Ellis trophy after the Springboks defeated England in the final earlier this month. IN PICTURES: World champions Springboks return home Before the World Cup, Kolbe also helped his club Toulouse to the French domestic title in June. The winger scored six tries in 16 league appearances. Kolbe also won the award for the best Top 14 player at the World Cup beating Fiji's Semi Radradra and France's Damian Penaud as well as winning the award for the try of the campaign.